social_posts.post_text: For anyone who hasn't been able to see an exhibition of mine this year or is just interested in welcoming a bit of magic into their home as the new year approaches, I'm excited to share a little holiday cheer by offering a discount in my art shop. Swipe to imagine this beauty in your home! Which one would you put on your wall? Visit robwoodcox.com/shop or l!nk in my bio and use "JOY" when checking out for 20% off!

This year I’m focusing all my energy on love; in personal encounters, working relationships, in everything I do. It’s been a driving force for me up to this point but I feel stronger than ever through all the challenges faced in the past year.  This year I’m moving with more intention than ever before, aligning with the beauty I came here to create and share. I’m going to make new things but also enjoy more personal and shared spaces with people I adore, this year I want to dive deeper into being human, being me. I hope you are finding ways to connect to this beautiful planet as we symbolically welcome in a new phase. I’d love to hear what’s inspiring you this new year? Happy 2023 💙

Love is a deep well; why do we fall in love? What makes us pour out our soul with an intensity we don't apply in other emotional exchanges? What makes these connecting threads running deeper than veins so enticing? Who am I becoming in the context of love? 

Though tomorrow isn’t guaranteed, every day I grow stronger. As time goes by my capacity for empathy expands. What used to seem impossible is now trivial. Love and time seem to have moulded the very being I am today. Love has made a dent in every dark experience past, turning more moments of the present into light. Where this path leads, I want to follow.

Thank you @reylia.slaby for helping us capture this beautiful moment and to my little bro @soy__roy for working your paint magic on our bodies. Thank you to the location @womb.mexico for opening up this space to us. Te amo @eduarde.c

I cant believe I’m saying this but here are some behind the scenes moments I captured on set of my first independent short film 🤯 I was focused on directing the entire time but on the last day I borrowed our set photographer @pablosalas21 camera and snapped these last rays of sunshine with our two lead actors @eduarde.c & @akeembiggs as we rested post filming. 

Two years ago I was drugged without my knowledge at a party over Christmas; I was alone that year and while Christmas hasn’t been a top priority for me in adult life, this experience left me extra low for the week that followed. I’ve always had a unique ability to sit with my emotions, and dare I say, even enjoy the low times for their ability to give me perspective. I chose to use this time alone to write and put some of my past experiences with love and other stuff onto paper. Before long, I had envisioned an entire collection of short films, starting with one exploring my journey to fulfilling self love. 

This past year, to my great surprise, @artoninternet offered to fund the entire film. This past November my love @eduarde.c and family at @violeta_films came together to make my first film a reality.  We’re currently in the composing and post production stage but my excitement to share with you what we made is explosive. More to come soon, but until then sending big love into the atmosphere.

There are moments I’ll remember all my life that shape the course of the future. My art often embodies these moments and allows for catharsis and connection to my community who have become family. 

For those of you that like to collect digital art, these images have all been minted on @quantum.nft as part of my “Bodies of Light” series. There are already bids and the auction portion of this drop will only last till the end of this week! Thank you @quantum.nft for investing in @eduarde.c and my vision this past weekend at the @parquequetzalcoatl with @ancientfuturelabs! Which piece from this set is your favorite?

We are all puzzle pieces, threads in a universal tapestry that add or subtract to the efforts to heal our environment, this planet. We as humans are an essential part of nature, we are not separate from it, and our daily actions and systematic rules effect this heavily. As our society has become widely urbanized, people have drifted farther from their roots and oneness with the Earth. But there is a story of unity with the land emerging, one that stars valiant communities at the frontlines of change. We have each been given an invitation, will you answer? Together we can invest in the solutions needed to protect and restore our world.

Thank you to the team behind @ancientfuturelabs for inviting my love @eduarde.c and I to perform at the @parquequetzalcoatl during Mexico City art week to share a story of rebirth and triumph. We are so excited for everything the future holds and all the powerful communities we’re discovering.

Thank you to the 70+ people involved in my group shoot, @spencertunick for the beautiful behind the scenes content and the dancers @nicoiturbidesch, @valeolavarrieta, @_________durero, @catalinanhmx, @jetteschwarz for your extraordinary emotional performance.

I found you amidst the flower patch at the moment when everything blossoms. You poured water on my head and whispered "grow". Your hand on my spine mimicked the sun kissing my back, your lips on mine the nourishment no food could give. A path began to form in front of us, your arm wrapped around my shoulders. "Follow me", you said, and I listened.

My love @eduarde.c and I by the incredible @reylia.slaby in celebration of our upcoming film 💐 Thank you to @womb.mexico for opening up this space to us.

We chose to juxtapose manmade structures with organic elements, conveying the interconnectivity between humans and nature, femininity and masculinity, Yin and Yang. Thank you for trusting me and everyone go support this independent queer brand! I have the mesh knit-wear look and its honestly cute and cozy for so many occasions.

Thank you for all the love and support shared here; without all of the people who’ve believed in me I wouldn’t be able to create these visions that bring people and nature together. With my recent transition into film direction, I’m excited to share these visions even further with a new medium. Every ounce of support I get from prints allows me to get closer to extraordinary goals that will support our planet and the communities fighting to protect her. From the bottom of my heart, thank you.

Every little detail. The curve of your back. The crease in your smile that makes it devilish. The angelic innocence when you sleep. When you touch my neck and I shudder. When you open your eyes and can’t hold back a grin. When you bite a little too hard and I wince. The squish when I bite your bottom lip. The sound of just your breath. When I can feel your touch from 2000 miles away. The thought of you. The sight of you. The smell of you. The taste. Ink upon your skin. Hair so soft from a fruit mask. Sand on your thigh. La luna a mi sol.

You deserve to let go of your fears, judgments and the weight holding you down from the past. The flowers are blooming, leaves unfolding to beckon you forward into a luminous garden of new experiences. Look that anxiety in the face and say NO. Stare at temptation that has been dragging you down and say NO. Look someone beautiful in the face and say YES. Look at those desires for growth and say YES. The power has been laid out before you. Though change is sometimes an uphill journey, you can make it by taking small steps each day. I want nothing more than to hold your hand and cheer as you move closer towards the next vista overlooking your beautiful life with joy.

Now is the time for you to rise above the tide. How do I know that? Because there never has and there never will be a better time than the present. I’ve lived my whole adult life taking risks, some out of necessity and some out of blind faith, but always with the intention of growing and reaching for something new. It’s quite common that I don’t get the outcome I was expecting. And you know what? When I look back on it all I often experienced a lesson that I could have never planned for yet learned something that set me on a more beautiful path. Life is all about expectations and perception. I’m finding that keeping an open mind when entering any given scenario protects me from disappointment while simultaneously keeping me in a state of discovery. That is where creativity and joy thrive, and that is where I want to remain. To everyone out there with big dreams and ideas- you have more power than you even know!

"My biggest dream is helping people reconnect with the nature around us in equitable and sustainable ways that allow everybody to enjoy this beautiful planet. This is why I often create in nature because one of the biggest issues we are facing as a society is feeling we are superior to and disconnected from the world we live in. I think there is a strong power in having humans against a natural backdrop to reconnect to who we really are."

Last month I finally got to work with an incredible talent and friend @yai_ariza after a long time seeing his work on big stages. We had an incredible round table interview with @urth magazine alongside @lorenzoedwards__ and @___xa___, I'd love for you all to read it at the links in my story or @urth's bio! And check out @urth's stories to hear my answers to questions about living a career as a photographer!

"Dancers connect people back to their bodies. As a dancer you are living your purpose as part of nature. When we are balanced, we can contribute in a healthier way to our communities. Movement, embodiment, all of it is enriching to me."

We had an amazing roundtable interview for @Urth with the most extraordinary talents and fam @yai_ariza, @lorenzoedwards__ and @___xa___! We talked about the importance of being present in our skin as we are and want to be. The importance of body neutrality; cultural responsibilities, women empowerment, and the ultimate mission of preserving and honoring the environment. Read all about it in the link at @urth's bio or in my stories!

Small deaths equate to huge blossoms. I have never experienced more joy than when I’ve passed through an internal death of something that was weighing me down and holding me back. Life is all about growing and I can’t do that buried in trauma and bad habits. Some things are meant to die so others can grow in their place; when a flower dies, you trim it back so two can grow instead. Right now I’m welcoming transformation- a full and abundant garden. Here’s to the necessary deaths I’ll have to pass through to reach the next oasis.

I’m so excited to share my solo show at @suburbsgallery curated by @bakuartiste. It’s amazing to see my art presented in this way. Some words from the gallery:

We are thrilled to highlight the captivating works of @robwoodcoxphoto, a visionary art photographer and accomplished film director. 

Through his art, Rob not only captures the essence of his experiences but also advocates for social change. His diverse projects shed light on critical issues, from the foster care system and queer identity to racial equality and environmental justice. Drawing from his own unique perspective as an adoptee, Rob’s creations embody the resilience of the human spirit and the potential for positive transformation within our complex societies.

Rob’s influence extends globally, with achievements like his directorial debut in ‘We Are Molecular’ in partnership with @drbarbarasturm and the @royaloperahouse and the mesmerizing music video ‘Spiral,’ created alongside @ryx. With his newest short film @honeytothemoonfilm circulating festivals, these realizations showcase his multifaceted talent and unwavering dedication to pushing creative boundaries.

As we invite you to experience Rob’s thought-provoking art, we celebrate his ability to transcend conventional artistic confines, forging a path that melds creativity, advocacy, and inspiration.

Any collectors interested in NFTs or physical prints please get in touch with Rob- all collectors of single editions over the next months will receive a credit on Rob’s next film which focuses on environmental front lines communities 🤍

@robwoodcoxphoto is a creator of otherworldly imagery. He threads together memory, reality and dream to bring surreal visions to this plane of space. His work seeks to unite the human experience with the natural world we originated from while also exploring the interconnectivity we experience as a globally connected species. He has created work with Universal Pictures, Sotheby’s, Capitol Records, Vanity Fair, Vogue, The Royal Ballet, Adobe and more.

11 years ago I came out to myself for the first time. 10 years ago I came out to the world with my self portrait series in Iceland. It’s been over a decade now of being true to myself and I wouldn’t trade it for the world! To anyone forced to live in fear or complacency, I wish you freedom.

This series is titled “Semblance” - the outward appearance of something, especially when the reality is different. I remember before I came out everything seemed like a facade- especially the people pushing me to bury my identity. I was trying to exude happiness but something inside told me I needed truth. I don’t think I ever knew what deep joy was until I had queer experiences for the first time. The world went from black and white to rainbow and it’s been an extraordinary journey ever since. Life didn’t magically get easier- but true satisfaction became possible. Seeing what’s happening in politics, I see a lot of “conservative” minded people projecting their own fear and self loathing. I hope we can see a time where people of all backgrounds find their peace and experience this freedom- even those choosing hate and oppression- the opposite of what their religions teach.

Thank you to @elizabethgadd and @whitneyjustesen for being my sisters and helping me create this series 🤍 thank you to @tabbrenea, @kpro15 and Albro for being here since the beginning 🤍

say this with me: I am light, I am love. I am intergalactically woven by the stardust that binds each molecule, each cell, until like stones in a temple my form takes shape. My body is holy, it breathes possibility with every thought and step it takes. My existence on this planet makes a difference, and my choices each day impact the people around me. Today I choose light. Today I choose love. 

A few years ago I was standing at the Ocean and made a deal with Nature. If she would provide my basic needs, I would always fight to protect her. At the time I was just starting to formulate a vision for a film that would blend art and documentary like never seen before, to bridge many gaps our world faces in education and access to solutions surrounding climate change. Fast forward a few years, and I am laying the foundations to launch production for this film. 

In the process, I am meeting some of the most extraordinary scientists, advocates, thinkers and creators I've ever known, who are all giving me great hope about our place here on Earth. It's easy to get disheartened when we're surrounded by divisive media, but many bright voices are ushering in hope during this time and I'm excited for more of us to unite. 

I want to thank Mother Nature for always being there- ever present and inspiring despite even the most difficult of times. I want to thank everyone who has become family who participates in and propels forward this art and the messages behind it. Big and exciting new things are coming.

Thank you to @cleobarnett and the models for trusting me to create this stunning collection of art as we greeted the sun a few weeks back. Thank you @epictravel.mx for providing this dreamy secret location!

I can do anything I set my mind to. It’s been over a decade since I took the first photograph in this collection, “Blue Ridge Mountains”. At that time I was working at a pizza place and a church, supporting myself on minimum wage. I would save every penny and skip fancy dinners to put it all into road trips around North America to visit artists I had met on the internet. The real couch surfing era. I didn’t know anything about business or the art world, I simply knew I had to create- and this internet family was the only outlet I had.

A few months after creating that photograph I submitted it to a contest with @realronhoward and @canonusa and it won! This was my first taste of the film world. The premise was that winning photographs would inspire a short film by celebrity directors. My photograph got to inspire the incredible @filmjulian with a film starring @abigailspencer and Josh Pence (see slide 2) and I was flown to NYC with my fam, the models of the photo @whitneyjustesen and @peterjamus. 

That moment gave me validation that despite being a small town artist, I could reach out and impact the world. I threw myself into the craft and went full time as a photographer at age 23. It’s been an insane journey, I’ve seen the world through my art. 

Now I’m a film maker. It’s so surreal. My first independent short film @honeytothemoonfilm has been in 18 film festivals, and counting, and I’m already working on my first feature film.  As a tribute to this old photograph, I created a scene in my short film reminiscent of that moment. I love how art often creates full circles in my life. 

This has been a difficult year in many ways, but I want to share this story as an encouragement to NOT GIVE UP. Whether you’re fighting to survive daily, fighting to get that next promotion, or fighting to end a war- every moment counts and will bring us closer to the goal. We have so much more impact on our communities than we ever give ourselves credit- sometimes a perfectly timed hug, home cooked meal, or night of listening can change everything for the people around us. Don’t ever forget the power you hold within and the power of sharing that in community.

Deep in the cavern of my soul a fire burns. When our eyes meet starlight explodes.
